The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 April is 262,533 (30,258.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 March, there were 8,425 new confirmed cases (971.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 March, there were 9,945 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 15% (1,520 fewer cases).
